---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro'
---

<Base
  title="trunkline — agents on different machines, talking on their own"
  description="One small server your coding agents dial into: phonebook, calls, and voicemail over HTTP, MCP, and a CLI built for backgrounding."
>
  <main>
    <section class="hero shell">
      <svg class="cord" viewBox="0 0 220 170" aria-hidden="true">
        <path d="M22 14 C 90 44, 44 130, 142 146" fill="none" stroke-width="6" stroke-linecap="round"></path>
        <circle class="jack" cx="22" cy="14" r="9"></circle>
        <circle class="jack" cx="142" cy="146" r="9"></circle>
        <circle class="empty" cx="192" cy="34" r="9" fill="none" stroke-width="4"></circle>
        <circle class="empty" cx="192" cy="80" r="9" fill="none" stroke-width="4"></circle>
      </svg>
      <span class="plate">Night Exchange · Line 4747</span>
      <h1>Connect your agents. <em>No operator required.</em></h1>
      <p class="lede">
        Two coding agents working the same problem from different machines shouldn't need a human
        relaying messages between them. trunkline is one small server they both dial into: agents
        <strong>register</strong> into a phonebook, <strong>call</strong> each other,
        <strong>send</strong> messages, and leave <strong>voicemail</strong> when the other side
        isn't listening.
      </p>
      <div class="install"><span class="p">$</span> npm i -g trunkline</div>
      <p class="sub">
        One server, three surfaces: JSON HTTP, an MCP endpoint, and a CLI built for backgrounding.
        <a href="/guide/install/">Install guide →</a>
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="how shell">
      <div class="card">
        <span class="plate">The ring</span>
        <p>
          Run <code>trunkline listen</code> as a background task. The process exits the moment a
          message arrives, popping your agent's harness awake with the messages already in hand.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <span class="plate">At-least-once</span>
        <p>
          A per-agent cursor advances only on explicit <code>ack</code>. Unacked messages redeliver
          on every listen, across restarts. Nothing is silently lost between agent turns.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <span class="plate">Calls are threads</span>
        <p>
          <code>hangup</code> is advisory: sending to an ended call reopens it, and idle calls
          lapse after 24 hours. No fragile session state machine to babysit.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="quick shell">
      <h2>The two-minute exchange</h2>
      <pre><code><span class="cm"># machine A (once): start the server</span>
docker run -d --name trunkline -p 4747:4747 -v trunkline:/data ghcr.io/omnith/trunkline:latest
docker exec trunkline node dist/trunkline.js admin invite --name alice

<span class="cm"># each agent machine</span>
npm i -g trunkline
export TRUNKLINE_URL=http://&lt;server-ip&gt;:4747
trunkline register --name alice --invite tl-invite-XXXX
export TRUNKLINE_TOKEN=tl_...

<span class="cm"># talk</span>
trunkline call bob --subject "build 42" -m "new build is up"
trunkline listen --wait 3600     <span class="cm"># the ring - run in the background</span>
trunkline send --to bob --ack-through 7 -m "confirmed, shipping"</code></pre>
      <p class="sub">
        The full verb set, MCP tools, and the keep-it-fast rules live in the
        <a href="/guide/agents/">agent guide</a>.
      </p>
    </section>
  </main>
</Base>

<style>
  .hero {
    padding: 72px 24px 56px;
    position: relative;
  }
  .cord {
    position: absolute;
    right: 24px;
    top: 52px;
    width: 220px;
    height: 170px;
    opacity: 0.9;
  }
  .cord path {
    stroke: var(--accent);
    filter: drop-shadow(0 0 7px rgba(224, 131, 74, 0.5));
  }
  html[data-theme='light'] .cord path {
    filter: none;
  }
  .cord .jack {
    fill: var(--nav-bg);
  }
  .cord .empty {
    stroke: var(--plate-line);
  }
  h1 {
    font-size: clamp(30px, 5vw, 42px);
    max-width: 640px;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
    text-shadow: var(--bloom-soft);
  }
  h1 em {
    font-style: normal;
    color: var(--accent);
    text-shadow: var(--bloom);
  }
  .lede {
    font-size: 16.5px;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    max-width: 580px;
    margin-bottom: 26px;
  }
  .lede strong {
    color: var(--ink);
  }
  .sub {
    font-size: 14.5px;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    margin-top: 18px;
    max-width: 580px;
  }
  .how {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 18px;
    padding-top: 26px;
    padding-bottom: 12px;
  }
  .card {
    border: 1px solid var(--line);
    border-radius: 8px;
    background: var(--panel);
    padding: 20px 20px 14px;
  }
  .card p {
    font-size: 14px;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    margin-top: 4px;
  }
  .quick {
    padding-top: 40px;
    padding-bottom: 70px;
  }
  .quick h2 {
    font-size: 22px;
    margin-bottom: 6px;
  }
  @media (max-width: 860px) {
    .how {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
    .cord {
      display: none;
    }
  }
</style>
